title.narrative: Output 2.3: NUTRITION By 2022, Nutrition national policies and institutional capacities are strengthened

description.narrative: National capacities to deliver nutrition interventions increased through upgraded information systems, revision of nutrition protocols and guidance, enhanced skills of service providers to counsel parents on adequate nutrition and child development, evidence generation and the school screening initiative. UNICEF-supported nutrition programmes reached 312,529 primary caregivers of children 0-23 months of age (through individual nutrition counselling) and 12 million school-aged children (through nutritional screening and referral). Multiple nutritional campaigns reached over 8 million people, reinforcing the importance of proper feeding practices for children and stimulating demand for nutritious food. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/09/2019
